Julius Evola (correctly) states that the crisis of puberty is repeated every time one falls in love. He also refers to copulation using similar language: "the trauma of coitus", "the crisis of coitus". Dr. Ray Peat cites W.D. Denckla on a "diabetes-like" state setting at puberty.

Another fun association between Evola and Ray Peat is Evola claiming that alcohol "can act as a hormone" favorizing the process of erotic intoxication and a production of sexual desire, similar to Peat seeing CO2, caffeine, or Niacinamide acting similarly to a hormonal substance.
